# See docs: https://docs.docker.com/build/concepts/context/#dockerignore-files
# The Docker Compose build-context is "the repository root", because we want
# to access the shared "packages" folder inside each service.
#
# Strategy: exclude everything, then allowlist only what the Dockerfiles need.

# ---------------------------
# 1. Exclude everything
# ---------------------------
*

# ---------------------------
# 2. Re-include service source code
# ---------------------------
!services/121-service/
!services/mock-service/

# ---------------------------
# 3. Re-include shared packages
# ---------------------------
!packages/eslint-config-121-platform/

# ---------------------------
# 4. Exclude generated/dependency files (even inside allowlisted folders)
# ---------------------------
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output
**/.swc
**/.angular
**/www
**/.eslintcache
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Sensitive / unnecessary files
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.DS_Store
**/.vscode
